    "body": "### Problem\n\nI used this file for testing: https://github.com/json-iterator/test-data/blob/master/large-file.json\r\n\r\nWithout any configuration NeoVim is able to instantaneously open the file but adding a single option to init.lua makes NeoVim to struggle opening it:\r\n```\r\nvim.opt.wrap = false\r\n```\r\n\r\nAdditionally removing more that roughly ten lines introduces lags. With enabled line wrapping deletion happens  instantaneously\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nissue.lua:\r\n```lua\r\nvim.opt.wrap = false\r\n```\r\n\r\n1. nvim --clean large-file.json\r\n2. nvim --clean -u issue.lua large-file.json\r\n\r\nObserve the difference between startup time. \r\nWith disabled line wrapping it takes for NeoVim a couple seconds to open the file on my machine.\r\n\r\nTry selecting about 10 lines or more in Visual Selection mode and delete it.\r\nWith disabled line wrapping it lags.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nPerformance should be identical or even better when disabling line wrapping since it often gets recommended in \"Optimizing Vim\" guides.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.0-dev-242+g22170efb4\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nYes, v9.0.1420\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.13.0-dev\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
